name: N-(9-fluorenylmethoxycarbonyloxy)succinimide
Reason: 9-Fluorenylmethoxycarbonyloxy group can increase the melting point due to the presence of a fluorenyl group, which can enhance pi-pi interactions and rigidity. The fluorenyl group can contribute approximately +30°C to the melting point. The carbonyl group can also contribute to the melting point due to the potential for hydrogen bonding and dipole-dipole interactions, estimated at around +10°C. The succinimide group can also participate in hydrogen bonding, which might add approximately +10°C.
